  "session_header": "[SESSION_HEADER]\nTimestamp: 1492 DR, Mirtul 15, 12:05:00\nLocation: The Athenaeum of Whispered Tomes\nStatus: Lvl 1 Fighter | HP: 12/12 | XP: 0/300 | Gold: 10gp",
  "resources": "HD: 1/1, Potions: 0, Exhaustion: 0",
  "narrative": "Midday (12:05:00) in the Athenaeum of Whispered Tomes—you take a breath, deciding that honesty might be the best currency with someone who has spent decades judging the worthiness of seekers.\n\n\"The truth,\" you say slowly, \"is that I've been having... dreams. Visions of something ancient stirring in the dark. Fragmented images—a sealed door, runes that seem to writhe when I close my eyes, and a voice calling out in a language I don't recognize but somehow understand.\"\n\nYou pause, gauging her reaction. \"I don't know what it means. But these dreams started three weeks ago, and they're getting stronger. I came to the Athenaeum because if there's any record of such things—any warning that was sealed away—I'll find it.\"\n\nArchivist Thessa's expression shifts almost imperceptibly. The practiced neutrality falters, replaced by something that might be concern—or perhaps recognition. She removes her spectacles, setting them carefully on the desk.\n\n\"Dreams, you say,\" she murmurs. \"What else have you seen?\" Her voice has dropped, become less formal. \"These visions—do they follow any pattern? Specific symbols, perhaps? A color that recurs?\"",
